properties.Name: FastaNucleicAminoAcidCode
properties.Description:
The amino acid codes used by the FASTA file format.

A --> Alanine
B --> Aspartic acid (D) or Asparagine (N)
C --> Cysteine
D --> Aspartic acid
E --> Glutamic acid
F --> Phenylalanine
G --> Glycine
H --> Histidine
I --> Isoleucine
J --> Leucine (L) or Isoleucine (I)
K --> Lysine
L --> Leucine
M --> Methionine/Start codon
N --> Asparagine
O --> Pyrrolysine (rare)
P --> Proline
Q --> Glutamine
R --> Arginine
S --> Serine
T --> Threonine
U --> Selenocysteine (rare)
V --> Valine
W --> Tryptophan
Y --> Tyrosine
Z --> Glutamic acid (E) or Glutamine (Q)
X --> any
* --> translation stop
- --> gap of indeterminate length

Columns.Name: FastaNucleicAminoAcidCode
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a FASTA nucleic amino acid.

Columns.Name: FastaNucleicAminoAcidName
Columns.Description: The name of a FASTA nucleic amino acid.

Columns.Name: FastaNucleicAminoAcidDescription
Columns.Description: The description of a FASTA nucleic amino acid.
